 framework of wetting of real surfaces, where physical and chemical heterogeneity is essential. Wetting of rough/heterogeneous surfaces is discussed through the use of the variational approach developed recently by the author. It allows natural and elegant grounding of main equations describing wetting of solid surfaces, i.e. Young, Wenzel and Cassie-Baxter equations. The problems of superhydrophobicity, wetting transitions and contact angle hysteresis are discussed in much detail, in view of novel models and new experimental data.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aHysteresis. 0aSolid-liquid interfaces. 0aSurface tension. 0aWetting. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / General.2bisacsh  aCassie Wetting.  aContact Angle Hysteresis.  aElectrowetting.  aNon Stick Droplets.  aSuperhydrophobicity.  aSurface Tension.  aSurface Wetting.  aWenzel Wetting.  aWetting Dynamics.  aWetting Transitions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Studies in Mathematical Physics eBook-Packagez978311064530908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Physical Sciences 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023851808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Physical Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637212oZDB-23-GPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE MATHEMATICS, PHYSICS, ENGINEERING 2013z9783110317282oZDB-23-DMI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MATHEMATIK, PHYSIK, INGENIEURWISS. 2013z9783110317275oZDB-23-DMP0 cprintz978311025853040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025879040uhttps: